  "summary": "TPC-H workload is dominated by lineitem scans (6M-60M rows) with selective date and range predicates. Q1 is a pure aggregation scan (bottleneck: full table scan + 8 aggregate functions); Q3 is a 3-way join with medium selectivity filters (bottleneck: lineitem hash join); Q6 is a filtered scan with complex predicates (bottleneck: SIMD-friendly multi-predicate evaluation). With 64 cores, 44 MiB L3 cache, and AVX512 support, primary optimization levers are: (1) morsel-driven parallel scan+filter with SIMD for Q1/Q6, (2) parallel hash join with early filtering and bloom filters for Q3, (3) partial aggregation to reduce synchronization overhead. HDD storage argues for columnar layout with compression on low-cardinality columns (l_returnflag, l_linestatus, c_mktsegment)."
